         <abstract id="aspace_e7100827b55366db68969ce9b270a629">Detailed correspondence, diaries, photographs, and collected material document the life and work of a young, single woman missionary in China. Elsie Clark Krug was an American Methodist missionary in Fuzhou (Foochow) from 1912 to 1918. She taught at Hwa Nan College, then in its preliminary stages a mission-supported college for women.</abstract>
         <origination label="Creator">
            <persname rules="aacr" source="local">
               <part localtype="agent_person">Krug, Elsie Clark, 1888-</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
